/*
:name: unnamed_tuple_type_field
:type: error
:error: tuple-type field must be named
:help: name each field
*/
// A tuple used as a TYPE must have NAMED fields (`name:T`). A bare type entry
// like `(signed, signed, signed)` has no field name and is malformed — use an array
// `[N]T` for N uniform elements, or name each field. (Named fields `x:signed` and
// `x=nil` are fine; only the bare-type form errors.)
mut x:(signed, signed, signed) = (1, 2, 3)
cassert(x[0] == 1)
